    <text xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"><body>
<div type="original">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/><lb n="1" xml:id="l-1"/>
<ab>Dinsdag middag</ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="2" xml:id="l-2"/>
<ab>Geachte Heer de Zwart,<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-o-1"/></ab><lb n="3" xml:id="l-3"/>
<ab>Het doet mij leed U gisteren bij <lb n="4" xml:id="l-4"/>mij zijt geweest zonder mij t’huis <lb n="5" xml:id="l-5"/>te treffen – ik wist niet U dien dag <lb n="6" xml:id="l-6"/>komen zoudt.</ab><lb n="7" xml:id="l-7"/>
<ab rend="indent">Nu hoor ik van Giesenberg<anchor n="2" xml:id="note-o-2"/> dat <lb n="8" xml:id="l-8"/>U morgen (Woensdag) naar alle <lb n="9" xml:id="l-9"/>gedachten weder hier op den Schenkweg <lb n="10" xml:id="l-10"/>komt. Daarom zal ik morgen <lb n="11" xml:id="l-11"/>zeker te huis blijven, daar <lb n="12" xml:id="l-12"/>ik U over een &amp; ander <lb n="13" xml:id="l-13"/>betreffende eene kleine vertimmering &amp;c<c type="kp">_</c> <lb n="14" xml:id="l-14"/>gaarne spreken wilde.</ab><lb n="15" xml:id="l-15"/>
<ab rend="indent">Met de meeste achting<c type="kp">_</c></ab>
<vg:whiteline/><lb n="16" xml:id="l-16"/>
<ab>Uw dr<c type="kp">_</c></ab><lb n="17" xml:id="l-17"/>
<ab>Vincent van Gogh<anchor n="3" xml:id="note-o-3"/></ab>
<vg:whiteline/><ab><pb f="2r" n="3" xml:id="pb-orig-2r-3" facs="#surf-pb-2r-3"/></ab><ab><pb f="2v" n="4" xml:id="pb-orig-2v-4" facs="#surf-pb-2v-4"/></ab></div>
<div type="translation">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>
<ab>Tuesday afternoon</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>Dear <rs type="pers" key="812 813">Mr de Zwart</rs>,<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-t-1"/></ab>
<ab>I am sorry that you came to see me yesterday and did not find me at home — I did not know you intended to come that day. </ab>
<ab rend="indent">Now I hear from <rs type="pers" key="472">Giesenberg</rs><anchor n="2" xml:id="note-t-2"/> that in all likelihood you will be coming to Schenkweg again tomorrow (Wednesday). I shall certainly stay at home tomorrow, because I should like to speak to you about one thing and another to do with some minor alterations. </ab>
<ab rend="indent">Yours respectfully.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>Your servant</ab>
<ab>Vincent van Gogh<anchor n="3" xml:id="note-t-3"/> </ab><pb f="2r" n="3" xml:id="pb-trans-2r-3" facs="#surf-pb-2r-3"/><ab><pb f="2v" n="4" xml:id="pb-trans-2v-4" facs="#surf-pb-2v-4"/></ab></div>
<div type="notes">
<note n="1" xml:id="n-1" target="#note-t-1">
<ab>We cannot say for sure whether the landlord at this time was <rs type="pers" key="813">Pieter Willem de Zwart</rs>, or his son <rs type="pers" key="812">Michiel Antonie de Zwart</rs>. We assume that it was the latter: a few letters addressed to him have survived.</ab></note>
<note n="2" xml:id="n-2" target="#note-t-2">
<ab>Here Van Gogh spells the name ‘Giesenberg’, but in <ref target="let412.xml">letter 412</ref> it is ‘Kiezenberg’. The person in question is <rs type="pers" key="472">Willem Kiesenberg</rs>. He lived at Schenkweg 134 (later Schenkstraat 15), very close to Van Gogh. See Visser 1973, pp. 23-30.</ab></note>
<note n="3" xml:id="n-3" target="#note-t-3">
<ab>Vincent added ‘van Gogh’ later.</ab></note></div></body></text></TEI>
